-- Slovenia Reduces Number of Ministries to Eleven, Delo Reports
-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 2012-01-27T07:28:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/slovenia-reduces-number-of-ministries-to-eleven-delo-reports.html
Slovenian lawmakers passed
legislation that reduces the number of ministries to eleven from
fifteen to speed up the formation of the new government, Delo
newspaper  reported , citing lawmakers. The most contentious issue
is a proposal to put the public prosecution department under the
control of the Interior Ministry, the Ljubljana-based newspaper
said.  Janez Jansa, whose party came second in the snap vote last
month, is likely to be confirmed as premier in tomorrowâ€™s vote
in parliament, according to Delo. The new government could be in
place by Feb. 10, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
